  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I delete my gmail only from one device and retain the same on other devices?",
  "response": "To delete your Gmail account from one specific device while keeping it on other devices, you can follow these steps. This process will remove your Gmail account from the selected device but won't affect its presence on other devices.\n\n### On Android:\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to your device's **Settings** app.\n2. **Accounts**: Tap on **Accounts** or **Users & Accounts**, depending on your device.\n3. **Select Gmail**: Tap on your Gmail account.\n4. **Remove Account**: Tap on **Remove Account** or **Delete Account**.\n5. **Confirm**: Confirm the removal when prompted.\n\n### On iPhone/iPad:\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to your device's **Settings** app.\n2. **Mail**: Tap on **Mail**.\n3. **Accounts**: Select **Accounts**.\n4. **Select Gmail**: Tap on your Gmail account.\n5. **Delete Account**: Tap on **Delete Account** and confirm.\n\n### On a Computer (Web Browser):\n1. **Sign Out of Gmail**:\n   - Open Gmail in your browser.\n   - Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner.\n   - Select **Sign out** or **Sign out of all accounts**.\n\n2. **Remove Account from Browser** (Optional):\n   - If your Gmail account is saved in your browser settings, you may need to remove it from there as well.\n   - Go to your browser's settings and look for the **Accounts** or **Passwords** section to remove the Gmail account.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- **Syncing**: Removing your Gmail account from a device will stop syncing emails, contacts, and other Google-related data on that specific device. However, your data will remain intact in your Google account and will continue to sync on other devices.\n- **Backup**: Ensure your data is backed up if you plan to use the account on another device or if you want to restore it later.\n\nBy following these steps, you can remove your Gmail account from one device without affecting its presence on other devices.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
